SofTech, Inc. Key Developments

SofTech, Inc. announced delayed 10-Q filing
Apr 17 17
On 04/17/2017, SofTech, Inc. announced that they will be unable to file their next 10-Q by the deadline required by the SEC.


SofTech, Inc. Announces Executive Changes
Aug 11 16
On August 5, 2016, Amy E. McGuire notified SofTech, Inc. of her intention to resign from her position of Chief Financial Officer, effective immediately, to accept a similar position at another company. Ms. McGuire has agreed to assist the company in a part time advisory role during an undefined transition period. Joseph P. Mullaney, the company’s President and Chief Executive Officer, will assume the duties of the company’s principal financial officer on an interim basis until such time as the company appoints a new Chief Financial Officer.


SofTech, Inc. Reports Unaudited Earnings Results for the Third Quarter and Nine Months Ended February 29, 2016
Apr 14 16
SofTech, Inc. reported unaudited earnings results for the third quarter and nine months ended February 29, 2016. For the quarter, the company reported total revenue of $912,000 against $925,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $292,000 against $270,000 a year ago. Loss from operations before income taxes was $310,000 against $356,000 a year ago. Net loss was $310,000 against $356,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted net loss per share was $0.34 against $0.40 per share a year ago. LBITDA was $249,000 against $171,000 a year ago. 

For the nine months, the company reported total revenue of $3,197,000 against $2,816,000 a year ago. Operating loss was $430,000 against $1,051,000 a year ago. Loss from operations before income taxes was $505,000 against $1,307,000 a year ago. Net loss was $505,000 against $1,307,000 a year ago. Basic and diluted net loss per share was $0.56 against $1.47 per share a year ago. LBITDA was $280,000 against $686,000 a year ago.


